WEBVTT

00:01.234 --> 00:04.647
Okay, everybody.
Big, big news.

00:05.138 --> 00:06.378
Leslie, would you
like to do the honors?

00:06.439 --> 00:07.747
No, I think you
should deliver the news.

00:07.907 --> 00:08.908
Yeah, but you're
the candidate.

00:08.975 --> 00:10.147
Yeah, but you're the
brilliant campaign manager.

00:10.210 --> 00:11.280
But you're the cutest.

00:11.344 --> 00:13.187
I love you.
I love you, too.

00:14.547 --> 00:16.549
Hey. Were you going
to tell us something?

00:16.716 --> 00:17.922
Right, Oh, yeah.

00:17.984 --> 00:22.763
The latest poll has us only two
points behind Bobby Newport.

00:22.822 --> 00:23.926
Two points!

00:23.990 --> 00:26.470
I know. You guys, we only have
one more day to close the gap,

00:26.526 --> 00:29.700
and we are gonna do so
in a one-time campaign blitz

00:29.763 --> 00:31.037
aboard the SS Knope.

00:31.698 --> 00:33.473
This is going to be our
home for the next 24 hours.

00:33.600 --> 00:36.479
And if we win, hopefully, it will be
the home that Ben and I share forever.

00:36.536 --> 00:38.015
Uh, what? It was
just an idea I had.

00:38.071 --> 00:39.709
We don't have to do it. Whatever.
We can talk about it.

00:39.773 --> 00:40.877
Okay. Here we go.

00:40.940 --> 00:44.752
We've come so far. I want
this so bad, I can taste it.

00:44.811 --> 00:47.519
When I close my eyes,
I can picture

00:47.580 --> 00:50.254
the flash of the cameras
at my swearing-in.

00:50.316 --> 00:54.287
And I can hear the sound of the
applause when I take my oath.

00:54.387 --> 00:56.890
And I can see,
in the crowd,

00:56.956 --> 01:00.369
President Obama
smiling at me.

01:00.827 --> 01:04.239
He made it. I didn't think he
would come, but he made it.

01:05.165 --> 01:06.644
Hey, buddy.

